></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The set of `n`-dimensional non-degenerate simplices in a simplicial\nset `X` is the complement of `X.degenerate n`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/AlgebraicTopology/SimplicialSet/Degenerate.html#SSet.nonDegenerate","kind":"def","line":39,"name":"SSet.nonDegenerate","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/AlgebraicTopology/SimplicialSet/Degenerate.lean#L39-L41"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/AlgebraicTopology/SimplicialSet/Degenerate.html#SSet.degenerate\"><span class=\"name\">SSet</span>.<span class=\"name\">degenerate</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/AlgebraicTopology/SimplicialSet/Basic.html#SSet\">SSet</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">X</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Functor/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.Functor.obj\">obj</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Opposite.html#Opposite.op\">Opposite.op</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/AlgebraicTopology/SimplexCategory/Defs.html#SimplexCategory.mk\">SimplexCategory.mk</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"An `n`-simplex of a simplicial set `X` is degenerate if it is in the range\nof `X.map f.op` for some morphism `f : [n] ⟶ [m]` with `m < n`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/AlgebraicTopology/SimplicialSet/Degenerate.html#SSet.degenerate","kind":"def","line":33,"name":"SSet.degenerate","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-commun